In England, in the seven days to 19 November, there were 19,386 new confirmed cases (34.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 November, there were 20,787 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (1,401 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 24 November is 20,269,112 (35,842.7 cases per 100,000 population).
